  "texts": [
    "In particular, their model suggests a framework for combining market equilibrium information with subjective investors' views by exploiting a Bayesian methodology.",
    "The computational evidence shows that the Black-Litterman model produces more stable and better-diversified portfolios than those constructed under Markowitz framework (Rebonato and Denev, 2014).",
    "An alternative to address estimation uncertainty parametrically is Monte Carlo resampling (Michaud, 1998), a procedure to determine portfolio weights as average weights from MPT results derived from bootstrapped market returns.",
    "In institutional active portfolio management, leveraged risk-based multi-asset allocations without return estimations are popular, namely Risk Parity (Qian, 2005; López de Prado, 2016; Dalio, 2004), Equal Risk Contribution (Maillard et al., 2010), and inverse-volatility weighting (Asness et al., 2012).",
    "A significant milestone is the Hierarchical Risk Parity (HRP) approach (López de Prado, 2016) aimed to improve the robustness of Risk Parity schemes in markets with fluctuating covariances."
